explanation.en:
This patient with diffuse lack of pigmentation and light sensitivity likely has oculocutaneous albinism (OCA), a condition characterized by impaired production or distribution of melanin, particularly eumelanin. Isolated OCA is most often caused by autosomal recessive mutations causing dysfunctional MELANIN SYNTHESIS within melanosomes (most commonly tyrosinase or P protein [regulates melanosome pH]), resulting in low or often completely absent melanin production. {{exhibit_1}}

Characteristic findings of OCA include diffuse white hair and skin and light irides. PHOTOPHOBIA is common because translucent irides allow in excess light. Because eumelanin protects against ultraviolet damage, patients with OCA are predisposed to SUNBURNS, as in this boy. Patients are also at increased risk for skin cancer, particularly squamous cell carcinoma.

(Choice A) The pathogenesis of vitiligo is multifactorial but likely involves CD8+ lymphocyte–mediated melanocyte apoptosis. Patches of depigmentation are characteristic; although the patches can coalesce to cause universal depigmentation, the process is gradual, chronic, and highly unlikely by age 10.

(Choice B) Formation of premelanosomes occurs normally in OCA. Melanized melanosome numbers may be decreased, which is secondary to reduced melanin production and not the primary mechanism of pigmentation defects in OCA.

(Choice C) Uptake of melanin by keratinocytes is disrupted in Chédiak-Higashi syndrome due to a defect in organelle trafficking. Patients have OCA, but recurrent pyogenic infections and coagulopathy would also be expected in early childhood.

(Choice E) Impaired differentiation of neural crest cells into melanocytes is a rare cause of scattered areas of depigmentation in piebaldism and Waardenburg syndrome. A white forelock is characteristic but is not seen in this patient. {{exhibit_2}} {{exhibit_3}} {{exhibit_4}}

explanation.zh:
该患者弥漫性色素缺乏和光敏感，可能患有眼皮肤白化病 (OCA)，这是一种以黑素（尤其是真黑素）产生或分布受损为特征的疾病。孤立性 OCA 最常由常染色体隐性突变引起，导致黑素体内的黑素合成功能障碍（最常见的是酪氨酸酶或 P 蛋白 [调节黑素体 pH 值]），导致黑素产生量低或完全缺失。 {{exhibit_1}}

OCA 的特征性表现包括弥漫性白发、皮肤苍白和虹膜颜色浅淡。畏光很常见，因为半透明的虹膜会允许过多的光线进入。由于真黑素可以防止紫外线损伤，因此 OCA 患者容易发生晒伤，就像这个男孩一样。患者患皮肤癌的风险也会增加，尤其是鳞状细胞癌。

(选项 A) 白癜风的发病机制是多因素的，但可能涉及 CD8+ 淋巴细胞介导的黑素细胞凋亡。色素脱失斑是其特征；尽管这些斑块可以融合导致普遍的色素脱失，但该过程是渐进的、慢性的，并且在10岁时极不可能发生。

(选项 B) 前黑素体的形成在 OCA 中正常发生。黑素化的黑素体数量可能会减少，这是黑素产生减少的继发表现，而不是 OCA 中色素沉着缺陷的主要机制。

(选项 C) 由于细胞器运输缺陷，角质形成细胞对黑素的摄取在 Chédiak-Higashi 综合征中受到破坏。患者患有 OCA，但在儿童早期也应预期会出现复发性化脓性感染和凝血病。

(选项 E) 神经嵴细胞分化为黑素细胞受损是斑驳病和 Waardenburg 综合征中散在色素脱失的罕见原因。白发绺是其特征，但在此患者中未见。 {{exhibit_2}} {{exhibit_3}} {{exhibit_4}}
